[schema] Add filtering by name to organizations query

Following the filtering format from other fields, now
the query asking for organizations supports an optional filter
for the field `name`. Example:

```
{
  organizations (
    filters:{
      name: "Example"
    }
  ){
    entities {
      name
      domains {
        domain
        isTopDomain
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Miguel Ángel Fernández <mafesan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutation for unmerging identities

Similar to `merge_identities`, this mutation accepts a list
of `uuid`s as input, allowing to unmerge several identities
from their parent unique identity at once, even if it is not
the same for all of them.

If the `uuid` from the parent unique identity is included in
the input list, this will have no effect.

Mutation example:

```
mutation unmergeIds($uuids: [String]) {
  unmergeIdentities(uuids: $uuids) {
    uuids
    uidentities {
      uuid
      identities {
        id
        name
        email
        username
        source
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Miguel Ángel Fernández <mafesan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutations for locking and unlocking unique identities

The input value for both `lock` and `unlock` mutations is the
`uuid` of the unique identity to be locked or unlocked.

Note that these actions also affect to the unique identity's
related objects such as identities, enrollments or its profile.

This `isLocked` new field has been added as a new filter for
the query asking for the unique identities.

Mutation examples:

"""
mutation lockId($uuid: String) {
            lockIdentity(uuid: $uuid) {
              uuid
              uidentity {
                uuid
                isLocked
              }
            }
          }
"""
"""
mutation unlockId($uuid: String) {
            unlockIdentity(uuid: $uuid) {
              uuid
              uidentity {
                uuid
                isLocked
              }
            }
          }
"""

Signed-off-by: Miguel Ángel Fernández <mafesan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add query to get the list of countries

This commit adds a query that allows to retrieve
the list of countries stored in the registry.
It is possible to filter by a country code or
by a term. The format of the query is as follows:

{
  countries(filters:{code: <code>, term: <term>}) {
    entities {
      code
      name
      alpha3
    }
  }
}

Signed-off-by: Santiago Dueñas <sduenas@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutation for generate affiliation recommendations

The mutation returns a job which returns a list of
recommendations which include the organizations where individuals
can be affiliated.

If the input list of individuals is empty, the job will be applied
to all the individuals in the registry.

The class `JobType` has been modified to include a new field
called `job_type`, which includes the name of the method that job is
executed for, and its value is obtained from the field `func_name`
inside the `Job` object.

This was needed because the resolver for jobs has to distinguish
between different jobs executed in different methods, as they
can return values in different ways.

Example for the new mutation:

```
mutation {
  recommendAffiliations(uuids: ["<uuid1>", "<uuid2>"]) {
    jobId
  }
}
```

```
{
  job(jobId: "<job_id>"){
    jobId
    status
    jobType
    result {
      __typename
      ... on AffiliationRecommendationType {
          uuid
          organizations
      }
    }
    errors
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Miguel Ángel Fernández <mafesan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutation for generate matching recommendations

The mutation returns a job which returns a list of
recommendations which include which individuals have identity
matches.

If the target list of individuals is empty, the job will be
applied to all the individuals in the registry.

Example for the new mutation:

```
mutation {
  recommendMatches(sourceUuids: ["<uuid1>",
                                 "<uuid2>"],
                   criteria: ["email", "name", "username"],
                   verbose: false){
    jobId
  }
}
```

```
{
  job(jobId: "<job_id>"){
    jobId
    status
    jobType
    result {
      __typename
      ... on MatchesRecommendationType {
          uuid
          matches
      }
    }
    errors
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Miguel Ángel Fernández <mafesan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutation for unify matching identities

The mutation returns a job which returns a list of identities
which have been merged with other matching identities according to
the specified criteria (a combination of email, name and username).

If the target list of individuals is empty, the job will be
applied to all the individuals in the registry.

Example for the new mutation:
```
mutation {
  unify(sourceUuids: ["<uuid1>",
                      "<uuid2>"],
        criteria: ["email", "name", "username"]){
    jobId
  }
}
```

Example for the query asking for the job result:
```
{
  job(jobId: "<job_id>"){
    jobId
    status
    jobType
    result {
      __typename
      ... on UnifyResultType {
          merged
      }
    }
    errors
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Miguel Ángel Fernández <mafesan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add query to get the list of jobs

Adds the 'jobs' query, which returns a paginated list
of all the jobs in the main queue.

The query has the following format:
query {
  jobs(pageSize: Int, page: Int) {
    entities {
      jobId
      status
      jobType
      errors
      result
    }
    pageInfo {
      page
      pagesize
      numPages
      hasNext
      hasPrev
      totalResults
    }
  }
}

Signed-off-by: Eva Millán <evamillan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutation for gender recommendations

The 'recommend_gender' mutation returns a job, which
returns a recommended gender for each individual uuid
based on their profile name. The 'JobResultType' on
the 'job' query now includes a 'GenderRecommendation'
type to retrieve the gender recommendations.

Example of the mutation:
```
mutation {
  recommendGender(uuids: ["uuid"]) {
    jobId
  }
}
```
Example of the job query:
```
query {
  job(jobId: "id") {
    jobId
    status
    jobType
    result {
      __typename
      ... on GenderRecommendationType {
          uuid
          gender
          accuracy
      }
    }
    errors
  }
}
```

Signed-off-by: Eva Millán <evamillan@bitergia.com>

[schema] Add mutation for genderize

The mutation returns a job with a list of identities
whose gender has been updated using the genderize.io
recommendations.

Example of the mutation:
```
mutation {
  genderize(uuids:["uuid1", "uuid2"]) {
    jobId
  }
}
```
Example of the job result query:
```
query {
  job(jobId: "id") {
    status
    jobType
    result {
      ... on GenderizeResultType {
        uuid
        gender
        accuracy
      }
    }
    errors
  }
}

